<h2 class="styleguide__header">Buttons</h3>

<div class="row">
	<h3>Basic</h3>
	<p class="span--4">
		Apply <code>.button</code> to get a basic blue button, adding the modifier <code>.button--secondary</code> adjusts the color to green. 
	</p>

	<div class="example-box example-box--vertical span--4">
		<div class="example-box__code">
			<pre class="code">

&lt;a class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;Click me&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;a class=&quot;button button--secondary&quot;&gt;Click me&lt;/a&gt;
			</pre>
		</div>

		<div class="example-box__example">
			<a class="button">Click me</a>
			<a class="button button--secondary">Nah, Click me</a>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="row">
	<h3>Download and External Link Buttons</h3>
	<p class="span--4">
		The modifier <code>.button--download</code> can be used to create a basic download button. 
	</p>

	<div class="span--4 ">
		<a class="button button--download">Click me</a>
		<a class="button button--download button--secondary">Click me</a>
	</div>
	
	<p class="span--4 break">
		You can also use <code>[rel="external"]</code> to indicate that a link goes somewhere offsite.
	</p>

	<div class="span--4">		
		<a class="button" rel="external">Click me</a>
		<a class="button button--secondary" rel="external">Click me</a>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="row">
	<h3>Disabled</h3>
	<p class="span--4">
		Buttons can be disabled using <code>.button--disabled</code>
	</p>
	<div class="span--4">	
		<a class="button button--disabled">Click me</a>
	</div>
</div>
	
<div class="row">
	<h3>Compact</h3>
	<p class="span--4">
		Compact buttons are used for things like white paper downloads at the bottom of a web application (see <a href="http://observatory.brain-map.org/visualcoding">BOb</a>)
	</p>
	<div class="span--4">
		<a class="button button--compact button--secondary">Click me</a>

		<a class="button button--compact button--download button--secondary">Click me</a>

		<a class="button button--compact button--secondary" rel="external">Click me</a>
	</div>
</div>

<div class="row">
	<h3>Icon Buttons</h3>
	<p class="span--4">
	Add an icon's classes to the anchor tag, icon buttons should <b>NOT</b> have text. It will be the wrong font and spaced incorrectly. If you need icon and text create a modifier like <code>.button--download</code>.
	</p>
	<div class="example-box break span--8">
		<div class="example-box__code">
			<pre class="code">

&lt;a class=&quot;button fa fa-download&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;button fa fa-wrench&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;button fa fa-cog&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a class=&quot;button fa fa-download&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;			
			</pre>
		</div>

		<div class="example-box__example">
			<a class="button fa fa-download"></a>
			<a class="button fa fa-wrench"></a>
			<a class="button fa fa-cog"></a>
			<a class="button fa fa-download"></a>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>



<div class="row">
	<h3>Stacked</h3>
	<p class="span--4">
		You can use the stacked button modifier <code>.button--stack</code> nested inside a header box to create a side bar menu, might be useful for things like the Brain Observatory front page.
	</p>
	
	<div class="example-box example-box--vertical span--8 break">
		<div class="example-box__code">
			<pre class="code">
&lt;div class=&quot;header-box header&quot;&gt;
  &lt;h2 class=&quot;header-box__header&quot;&gt; Button Stack &lt;/h2&gt;
  &lt;div class=&quot;header-box__content header-box__content--no-pad&quot;&gt; 

	&lt;a class=&quot;button button--stack&quot;&gt;Link 1&lt;/a&gt;

	&lt;a class=&quot;button button--stack&quot;&gt;Link 2&lt;/a&gt;

	&lt;a class=&quot;button button--stack button--secondary button--disabled&quot; rel=&quot;external&quot;&gt;Link 3&lt;/a&gt;

	&lt;a class=&quot;button button--stack&quot;&gt;Link 4&lt;/a&gt;

	&lt;a class=&quot;button button--stack&quot;&gt;Link 5&lt;/a&gt;

	&lt;a class=&quot;button button--stack&quot;&gt;Link 6&lt;/a&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
			</pre>
		</div>
	
		<div class="example-box__example">
			<div class="span--4">

				<div class="header-box header">
				  <h2 class="header-box__header"> Button Stack </h2>
				  <div class="header-box__content header-box__content--no-pad"> 

						<a class="button button--stack">Link 1</a>

						<a class="button button--stack">Link 2</a>

						<a class="button button--stack button--secondary button--disabled" rel="external">Link 3</a>

						<a class="button button--stack">Link 4</a>

						<a class="button button--stack">Link 5</a>

						<a class="button button--stack">Link 6</a>
				  </div>
				</div>
			</div>
	
		</div>
	</div>	
</div>

<h3>Tool Bars</h3>
<p class="span--4">
	By adding <code>&lt;div class=&quot;header-box__header-tools&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</code> to the header-box header you can insert buttons to make a tool bar.
</p>
<div class="row">
	<div class="example-box example-box--vertical span--8 break">
		<div class="example-box__code">
			<pre class="code">
	&lt;div class=&quot;header-box span--5&quot;&gt;
		&lt;h2 class=&quot;header-box__header&quot;&gt; 
			Some Header
			&lt;div class=&quot;header-box__header-tools&quot;&gt;
				&lt;a class=&quot;button button--tool-bar&quot;&gt;Reset&lt;/a&gt;
				&lt;a class=&quot;button button--tool-bar fa fa-cog&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
				&lt;a class=&quot;button button--tool-bar fa fa-expand&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
				&lt;a class=&quot;button button--tool-bar fa fa-close&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
			&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/h2&gt;
		&lt;div class=&quot;header-box__content&quot;&gt; 

		Lorem ipsum 

		&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
			</pre>
		</div>

		<div class="example-box__example">
			<div class="header-box">
			  <h2 class="header-box__header"> 
				Some Header
				<div class="header-box__header-tools">
					<a class="button button--tool-bar">Reset</a>
					<a class="button button--tool-bar fa fa-cog"></a>
					<a class="button button--tool-bar fa fa-expand"></a>
					<a class="button button--tool-bar fa fa-close"></a>
				</div>
			  </h2>
			  <div class="header-box__content"> 
				
				Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Facere modi quia eum quibusdam assumenda totam blanditiis dolorem ipsa provident autem, unde nobis, accusantium, esse at pariatur ex maxime omnis voluptate.

			  </div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>
<div class="row">
	<div class="span--8">
		<h3>Pagination Buttons</h3>
		<p>
			
		</p>

		<div class="example-box">
			<div class="example-box__code">
				<pre class="code">
				
&lt;div class=&quot;pagination&quot;&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button fa fa-chevron-left&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button pagination__current&quot;&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;4&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;5&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button fa fa-chevron-right&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;pagination&quot;&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button fa fa-chevron-left button--disabled&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button pagination__current&quot;&gt;1&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;2&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;3&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;4&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button&quot;&gt;5&lt;/a&gt;
	&lt;a class=&quot;button fa fa-chevron-right&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
				</pre>
			</div>
		
			<div class="example-box__example">
				<div class="pagination">
					<a class="button fa fa-chevron-left"></a>
					<a class="button">1</a>
					<a class="button">2</a>
					<a class="button pagination__current">3</a>
					<a class="button">4</a>
					<a class="button">5</a>
					<a class="button fa fa-chevron-right"></a>
				</div>

				<div class="pagination">
					<a class="button fa fa-chevron-left button--disabled"></a>
					<a class="button pagination__current">1</a>
					<a class="button">2</a>
					<a class="button">3</a>
					<a class="button">4</a>
					<a class="button">5</a>
					<a class="button fa fa-chevron-right"></a>
				</div>
		
			</div>
		</div>
		
	</div>
</div>
